What we have learnt till now in Shodan
Installation of Shodan in Python Environment :

$ easy_install shodan



BlackArch Environment :

# pacman -S python-shodan



To setup API Token :

shodan init<YOUR_API_KEY>



Shodan Info of your Account :

$ shodan info



To check version of Shodan :

$ shodan version



Count number of result we are going to get from search query : 

$ shodan count openssh



To download search results : 

shodan download bigipfile bigip



This was the quick recap of Shodan. We will dive more deeper in Shodan.








Host Enumeration :

To get information about any ip address

$ shodan host 1.1.1.1



Shodan parse dataset :

$ shodan myip

you can parse a file that was generated using download command.

$ shodan parse [OPTIONS] <filename>



Shodan serach query :

$ shodan search -h

$ shodan search [OPTIONS] <search query>



Shodan Scan command :

$ shodan scan -h

$ shodan scan [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...



Shodan Stats : 

$ shodan stats -h

$ shodan stats [OPTIONS] <search query>



Shodan GUI : 

https://www.shodan.io/



Shodan Report Generation : 




Shodan Images : 

Searchable images gallery of screenshots from crawled devices.




Shodan Exploits : A search engine that looks for exploits across a variety of vulnerability databases at once.



https://exploits.shodan.io/welcome




Shodan Extension :  https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/shodan/jjalcfnidlmpjhdfepjhjbhnhkbgleap



This was the quick recap of Shodan.

